==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English, from Latin ''[[contortus]]'', past participle of ''[[contorquere]]'', from ''[[com-]]'' + ''[[torquere]]'' (to twist).

===Verb===
{{en-verb|contort|contorts|contorted|contorting}}
#''(transitive)'' To [[twist]] in a [[violent]] manner; as, features contorted with fury.
#''(intransitive)'' To [[twist]] into or as if into a [[strain]]ed [[shape]] or [[expression]].

